entries.title: Two Britons among four killed in Australian helicopter collision
entries.description: Two British citizens were among four killed after two helicopters collided mid-air near a marine theme park in the Australian state of Queensland.

entries.title: FIFA to ask every country to name a stadium in honour of football great Pele, Infantino says
entries.description: FIFA plans to ask every country in the world to name a stadium in honour of the late football legend Pele, its president Gianni Infantino has said.

entries.title: Ukraine claims 400 Russian soldiers killed in barracks strike
entries.description: Scores of Russian soldiers were killed in a missile strike in the occupied Donetsk region in one of the deadliest attacks on the Kremlin's forces since the war began more than 10 months ago.

entries.title: Kim Jong Un sacks North Korea's second-most powerful military leader
entries.description: North Korea's Kim Jong Un has sacked the country's second-most powerful military official, according to state media.

entries.title: Martina Navratilova diagnosed with throat and breast cancer
entries.description: Tennis legend Martina Navratilova has been diagnosed with throat and breast cancer.

entries.title: Looted sarcophagus kept in US museum returned to Egypt
entries.description: An ancient sarcophagus was returned to Egypt from a museum in the US after authorities determined it was looted.

entries.title: UK Border Force officers patrol French beaches with local police for first time
entries.description: UK Border Force officers have joined patrols on French beaches for the first time in a bid to stem the flow of migrants crossing the Channel.

entries.title: Airport worker dies after being 'ingested' into plane engine
entries.description: An airport worker has died after being "ingested" into a plane engine in the US state of Alabama.

entries.title: Police chase Tesla for 15 minutes after driver turns on autopilot and 'goes to sleep'
entries.description: A Tesla driver in Germany has been accused of giving the 'auto' in autobahn a new meaning, by putting his car in control as he slept at the wheel.

entries.title: Thousands queue to see former pope Benedict's body lying in state
entries.description: Thousands of people are paying their respects to former Pope Benedict XVI as his body lies in state at the Vatican.

entries.title: Pele to lie in state at stadium of former club Santos ahead of funeral
entries.description: Thousands of football fans will say a final goodbye to Brazil legend Pele at the home of his former club Santos.

entries.title: Four dead after two helicopters collide in mid-air near Sea World theme park in Australia
entries.description: Two helicopters have collided near a marine theme park in the Australian state of Queensland, killing four people and leaving three others critically injured.

entries.title: British yoga teacher says it's a 'miracle' she's alive after boat propeller left her seriously injured
entries.description: A British yoga instructor says it is a "miracle" she is alive after being seriously injured by a boat propeller while snorkelling in Mexico.
